news.title: China Evergrande Group to detail debt restructure plan on March 22
news.para: Evergrande, which began one of China's biggest debt restructuring processes early last year, expects to sign a deal with general creditors by the end of March, with the restructuring to take effect from Oct 1, it added on Monday.

news.title: Raipur development body gives rebate on dues deposit by March 31
news.para: The allottees in Market, Boriyakhurd, Hirapur, Raipura and Transport Nagar Ranwabhata have the maximum outstanding amount under the old schemes. RDA chief executive officer Dharmesh Kumar Sahu said that the amount of surcharge is continuously increasing due to non-payment of regular payments in many projects.

news.title: More time to submit report on 'A' khatas in Bengaluru
news.para: Earlier, the civic agency had instructed them to prepare detailed reports on allegations that 'B' khata properties were illegally changed to 'A' khata. The reports were to be submitted to a review committee by 3pm on March 24.

news.title: Noida authority yet to get Rs 1,400 crore from 74 properties it has leased out
news.para: Those using the buildings and space deposited money in the beginning but stopped paying the rent later, the officials said, adding that notices had been sent to each of them.

news.title: Distribution delay as Pune civic body to reprint 4.5 lakh property tax bills
news.para: The new bills will be printed after the state government's decision to offer 40% tax discount for self-occupied properties. A notification will be soon issued.

news.title: Ludhiana civic body to roll out property ID cards from April 1
news.para: Interested residents can avail this card, which is similar to an ATM card, by paying a nominal charge of Rs 50. The basic purpose of this card is to give an ID to property holders of their records.

news.title: Chandigarh: Property tax bills to land in your mail from April
news.para: Taxpayers will be offered rebate — 20% for residential properties and 10% for commercial buildings — if they make the payment from April 1 to May 31. From June, defaulters will have to pay 25% penalty on the tax and 12% interest too.

news.title: Bankrupt, stressed realty projects on investors' radar
news.para: Despite the challenge of insolvency, these companies and their projects are still finding good interest from investors given the presence of tangible assets including the land parcels and unfinished structures with a certain portion of sales achieved.

news.title: Insurers to link property cover rates to past claims
news.para: According to industry sources, the revision follows the regulator’s directive that rates published by the insurance information bureau need not be treated as a minimum rate.

news.title: Real estate focussed fund Experion Developers set to acquire Dignity Buildcon
news.para: Experion Developers offered Rs 450 crore for the real estate developer Dignity Buildcon - a company engaged in developing commercial towers on Golf Course Extension Road of Gurgaon.

news.title: Brookfiled extends pact to buy IL&FS' headquarters till June
news.para: Project Holdings Seven (DIFC), which is an affiliate of Brookfield, had signed the agreement for 12,651.95 square meters land at plot No C-22, in the 'G' Block of Bandra Kurla Complex, Mumbai, together with the IL&FS Financial Centre in December 2021.

news.title: Another round of structural audits in highrise societies from April 1 in Gurugram
news.para: The administration has also sought suggestions of residents from the 15 societies that were covered during the first phase. Deputy commissioner Nishant Yadav said further action on the required repairs or changes would be decided based on the suggestions.

news.title: Livspace lays off about 2% of its overall workforce in a bid to drive profitability
news.para: A total of 36 staffers, including software engineering developers and directors from a team of 80 have been asked to leave the company, sources told ET.

news.title: Slum residents near JLN stadium in Delhi get eviction notice
news.para: On March 16, the officials sent the around 500 occupants of the 60 jhuggis an eviction notice. The residents of the slum, who have come to Delhi from West Bengal, Rajasthan and Bihar, have been asked to vacate the area before March 20.

news.title: Activists write to CM, centre opposing move to hand over Navi Mumbai wetlands for IT hub
news.para: Protesting against the project coming up on the "graves of mangroves and wetlands" of Uran, greens have said government-appointed site inspection committees have confirmed there will be destruction.
